          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ": “During COVID, the state’s ballot-receipt deadline and the court’s decision upholding it disenfranchise citizens by depriving them of their constitutionally guaranteed right to vote. Because the court refuses to reinstate the district court’s injunction, Wisconsin will throw out thousands of timely requested and timely cast mail ballots.”",
            "type": "text",
